Subject: Re: [T2] bleeding clutch question

On Sat, 25 Jan 2003, Mary Barbara wrote:

> The clutch on my Vanagon needs to be bled.  The Bentleys says to ONLY bleed
> with a pressure bleeder.  What happens if I don't?

It probably won't be bled completely.  It won't hurt to try it, though.

A vacuum bleeder works on exactly the same principle as a pressure
bleeder, BTW, except that it can apply more pressure across the system.
Vacuum bleeders are cheaper if it ends up that you need one.

George Lyle
